cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on visual object recognition using kernel methods, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of covariance operators and their approximation, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of convolutional features, which are commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE) and the task of image classification, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM).
